Class Argument

java.lang.Object
  project3.three.Node
      project3.lex.Token
          project3.lex.Argument
Direct Known Subclasses:
Constant, Identifier
public abstract class Argument
extends Token

An Argument token. This is not needed for assignment 1, but is included in the lex package to make it easier to read the code in project 3.

Syntax : Argument → Identifier | Constant 

 Domain Definition:
     type       : TokenType
     value      : String
     lineNumber : Integer
 
 Instance Invariant:
     ∀x (x instanceof Argument ⇒
                   x instanceof Identifier OR
                   x instanceof Constant
         )

createCopy

public static Argument createCopy(Argument argument)
                           throws ParserException
Creates a specific copy of the argument depending on the type of the argument.

Precondition: argument ≠ null
Postcondition: argument instanceof Identifier ⇒ result = new Identifier(argument)
argument instanceof Constant ⇒ result = new Constant(argument)
¬ argument instanceof Constant AND ¬ argument instanceof Identifier ⇒ result = null 		AND
